<span id="freeTextContainer6214326416185591770">Some of King&apos;s best stories are in this collection, notably <i>Rage</i>, written years before Columbine, <i>The Long Walk</i>, which is like <i>The Hunger Games</i> without the love triangle or the optimism, and <i>The Running Man</i>, which is much darker and much better than the movie that was (very, very loosely) based on it. These are all typically grim King stories, but without the supernatural flavor of most of his work.</span>
  <span id="freeText6214326416185591770" style="display:none">Some of King's best stories are in this collection, notably <i>Rage</i>, written years before Columbine, <i>The Long Walk</i>, which is like <i>The Hunger Games</i> without the love triangle or the optimism, and <i>The Running Man</i>, which is much darker and much better than the movie that was (very, very loosely) based on it. These are all typically grim King stories, but without the supernatural flavor of most of his work.</span>
