          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4064444017" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11528432644107627679">I love these books I love these books I love these books.<br/><br/>It has just occurred to me that I could consider this my favorite King novella collection, because... that&apos;s... what it is? Except some of these get a little lengthy to be considered novellas, but they&apos;re all bundled up so neat and so I would like to announce that The Bachman Books have surpassed Four Past Midnight as my favorite King novella collection.<br/><br/>I love every book in this collection. The Long Walk, is, obviously, my favorite book of</span>
  <span id="freeText11528432644107627679" style="display:none">I love these books I love these books I love these books.<br /><br />It has just occurred to me that I could consider this my favorite King novella collection, because... that's... what it is? Except some of these get a little lengthy to be considered novellas, but they're all bundled up so neat and so I would like to announce that The Bachman Books have surpassed Four Past Midnight as my favorite King novella collection.<br /><br />I love every book in this collection. The Long Walk, is, obviously, my favorite book of all time, but this time it did actually make me cry, so there's that. I'm sad that Rage is out of print, though I understand why it is. Roadwork is a tragedy and The Running Man is '1984, but Make It Stephen King'). I love it. I love it all. </span>
